latestPosts.caption:
Hair care is one of my favorite forms of self care 🤎⁣
⁣
I started my curly hair journey 6 years ago, in December of 2018 & I never really tried any new hairstyles besides just wearing it down curly. I’ve been trying different ways of styling my hair recently, including straightening, sock curls, braid outs, etc. & it’s honestly been refreshing to switch it up ✨

Summer is for the curlsss 🥥🌴😍⁣
⁣
Shared some products at the end that give me great hold (some give medium & some give strong) ⁣
⁣
Sharing my fav summer styling combos soon 🫶🏽

latestPosts.caption:
Gel cast is key, if you want your curls to last ⁣
⁣
If I don’t get a gel cast it’s usually because: ⁣
💧The leave in conditioner or curl cream was too heavy ⁣for my hair 
💧I used too much water when styling & watered down the gel ⁣
💧Product build up ⁣
💧The gel simply has no hold/is too light for my hair

latestPosts.caption:
💧 Low Porosity Hair Guide 💧 ⁣
⁣
This is how I hydrate my medium to low porosity hair & what works for me personally 🫶🏽 ⁣
⁣
When your hair is low porosity, the cuticle lays flat. This means that it is harder to hydrate the hair. However, once low porosity hair is properly hydrated, it holds only to that hydration well 🚿🫧🧼 ⁣
⁣
If you have low porosity, you will notice how water or heavy products take awhile to be fully absorbed! ⁣
⁣
What’s your hair porosity?

latestPosts.caption:
Beginner Curly Hair Routine⁣
⁣
This is just an example, but use whatever works for you 🫶🏽⁣
⁣
🫧 My ideal weekly shampoo is something that isn’t drying. @redken All Soft Mega Curls Shampoo is sulfate-free, so it gently cleanses the hair ⁣
⁣
💦 @redken All Soft Mega Curls Conditioner detangles, hydrates, & strengthens hair. It will help to improve hair’s manageability as well ⁣
⁣
🤍 I love all of @briogeo hair masks, but this one in particular is one I would use weekly because it offers protein & moisture balance ⁣
⁣
🧴 @innersenseorganicbeauty stylers are my favorite stylers. Both of these combinations have been favorites for years. If you prefer to scrunch out the crunch, use your favorite oil or serum after your hair is dry
